<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5248] Fix timestamp-based tomstone removal logic</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5248</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Quoting the description of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4671&quot; title=&quot;Improve removal of gcable tomstones during minor compaction&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4671&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4671&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In other words, we should force CompactionController.shouldPurge() to return true if min_timestamp(non-compacted-overlapping-sstables) &amp;gt; max_timestamp(compacted-sstables)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;but somehow this was translating in the code to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;if (sstable.getBloomFilter().isPresent(key.key) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; sstable.getMinTimestamp() &amp;gt;= maxDeletionTimestamp)
    return false;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which, well, is reversed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attaching the trivial patch to fix. I note that we already had a test that catched this (CompactionsTest.testDontPurgeAccidentaly), but that test was racy in that most of the time the compaction was done in the same second than the removal done prior to that and thus the compaction wasn&apos;t considering the tombstone gcable even though gcgrace was 0. I&apos;ve already pushed the addition of a 1 second delay to make sure the patch reliably catch this bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
